# Profiling Rules

## Philosophy

Never optimize by feeling.

Always measure first.

Profiling tells us:

- What is slow
- Why it is slow
- How often it happens
- Whether the fix actually worked

Performance decisions must be data-driven.

---

# Profiling Goals

Measure:

- FPS
- Frame time
- CPU time
- GPU time
- Script time
- Physics time
- Navigation time
- AI tick time
- Combat tick time
- Memory usage
- Node count
- Object pool usage
- Draw calls
- Save/load time

---

# Golden Rule

Before optimizing:

1. Reproduce the issue
2. Measure baseline
3. Identify bottleneck
4. Fix one thing
5. Measure again
6. Compare results

Never change multiple systems at once.

---

# Performance Budget

Target platform:

Android mid-range device.

Recommended budget:

```text
Frame Time:        <= 16.6 ms
Script Time:       <= 5 ms
Physics Time:      <= 3 ms
AI Tick:           <= 2 ms
Combat Tick:       <= 2 ms
Navigation Tick:   <= 3 ms
UI Update:         <= 2 ms
Save:              <= 500 ms
Load:              <= 3 sec
Memory:            <= 512 MB
```

---

# Profiling Levels

## Level 1: Quick Check

Use for daily development.

Measure:

- FPS
- Frame time
- Memory
- Node count
- AI tick
- Combat tick

---

## Level 2: Feature Profiling

Use before merging a feature.

Measure:

- New allocations
- New nodes
- New signals
- New timers
- New process callbacks
- New path requests

---

## Level 3: Stress Profiling

Use before release.

Measure:

- 300 Heroes
- 1000 Monsters
- 200 NPC
- 100 Buildings
- 3000 Loot
- 24-hour simulation

