# AI Profiling

Measure:

- Decision time
- Scheduler time
- Goal selection time
- Path request frequency
- Failed decisions
- Idle duration
- State changes
- Target switching

AI should not think every frame.

---

# Navigation Profiling

Measure:

- Path request count
- Path completion time
- Failed paths
- Stuck heroes
- Repath frequency
- Average travel time

Never call path recalculation every frame.

---

# Combat Profiling

Measure:

- Active combats
- Skill casts
- Damage calculations
- Target searches
- Status effect updates
- Projectile count
- Loot creation

Combat should use direct calls for high-frequency logic.

---

# UI Profiling

Measure:

- Open panel time
- List rendering time
- Widget count
- Rebuild count
- Inventory sort time
- Hero list refresh time

UI must update only when state changes.

---

# Save/Load Profiling

Measure:

- Save file size
- Save time
- Load time
- Serialization time
- Deserialization time
- Compression time
- Migration time

Save must not freeze gameplay.

---

# Memory Profiling

Track:

- Total memory
- Peak memory
- Node count
- Resource count
- Pool size
- Orphan nodes
- Persistent references

Memory should return near baseline after closing scenes.

---

# Object Pool Profiling

Measure:

- Pool hit rate
- Pool miss rate
- Pool growth
- Reuse count
- Exhaustion count

Pool miss spikes indicate wrong sizing.

---

# Signal Profiling

Watch for:

- Signals emitted every frame
- Repeated connections
- Dangling connections
- Global EventBus spam

Signals should represent events, not polling.

---

# Timer Profiling

Avoid hundreds of independent timers.

Prefer centralized scheduler.

Measure:

- Timer count
- Scheduler queue size
- Tick latency
- Starvation

---

# Regression Detection

A build fails profiling when:

```text
FPS drops > 10%
Memory increases > 15%
AI tick increases > 20%
Combat tick increases > 20%
Navigation failures increase
Save time exceeds budget
Node count grows unexpectedly
```

